# CODEOWNERS — required-reviewer rules
#
# Created in T4.8 of the agent-runtime remediation plan (find_p5_006).
#
# This file defines GitHub-required reviewers. The first matching pattern
# for any path wins. To enforce this in practice, also enable
# "Require review from Code Owners" in Settings → Branches → develop / main.
#
# Owner placeholders (`@usetheodev/*`) are GitHub team handles; replace
# with concrete logins or update the team membership as the org grows.

# ── Default fallback ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any file not matched by a more specific rule below requires a review
# from the maintainers team.
*                                       @usetheodev/maintainers

# ── Bounded contexts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
crates/theo-domain/                     @usetheodev/runtime-team
crates/theo-engine-graph/               @usetheodev/engine-team
crates/theo-engine-parser/              @usetheodev/engine-team
crates/theo-engine-retrieval/           @usetheodev/engine-team
crates/theo-governance/                 @usetheodev/runtime-team
crates/theo-agent-runtime/              @usetheodev/runtime-team
crates/theo-infra-llm/                  @usetheodev/runtime-team
crates/theo-infra-auth/                 @usetheodev/security-team
crates/theo-infra-mcp/                  @usetheodev/runtime-team
crates/theo-infra-memory/               @usetheodev/engine-team
crates/theo-isolation/                  @usetheodev/security-team
crates/theo-tooling/                    @usetheodev/runtime-team
crates/theo-application/                @usetheodev/maintainers
crates/theo-api-contracts/              @usetheodev/runtime-team

